Put a large #saucepan{} of water with a generous pinch of @salt{pinch} on to boil for the pasta. Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove} (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve the @tomato{2%medium}. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). Finely chop the @chives{some}(finely chopped).

> TIP: You can use also use scissors to chop the chives!

Heat a little @oil{a little} in a #frying pan{} on high heat. Add the @chorizo{60%g}, stir-fry until just turning crispy, ~{2-3%mins}. Lower the heat to medium, stir in the tomatoes, onion and a little knob of @butter{a little} (if you have some!). Add a good pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch} and mix it all up. Cover with a #lid{} (or #foil{}) then leave to cook until the onion is soft and the tomatoes have burst, stirring once or twice, ~{10-12%mins}.

Meanwhile, add the @spaghetti{200%g} to the pan of boiling water and cook for ~{8%mins}. Once cooked, reserve a ladleful of pasta water, then drain the pasta in a #colander{} and drizzle with a little @olive oil{a little} to stop it sticking together.

After ~{10-12%mins}, remove the lid from the frying pan and stir in the garlic, @tomato passata{1}(small can), a small pinch of @chilli flakes{1%small pinch} (don't add all of them, they are hot! You can add more later if required) and the @red wine vinegar{1%tbsp}. Increase the heat slightly and bring to the boil. Cook for ~{30%seconds} then add the @water{some} (see ingredients for amount).

Add the @King prawns{120%g} into the sauce, mix together and cook for a further ~{3-4%mins}. Taste and season with more salt and pepper if necessary. Add some more chilli here if you want to!

> IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle!

Once the prawns are cooked, stir the drained spaghetti into the sauce and add a splash of the reserved pasta water if it looks a little dry! Toss everything together well then remove from the heat. Mix the chives into the spaghetti then divide between your #bowls{}. Buon Appetito!